# config/dns.seed.example
# Bring-up seed records for Technitium DNS.
#
# This file is a first-deploy convenience: at bootstrap it is applied directly
# into Technitium so DNS works immediately, and imported into NetBox so the
# ongoing NetBox -> Technitium reconcile sees the same records as desired state.
#
# After bring-up, NetBox is the source of truth. Editing this file later and
# expecting reconcile to honor it will not work - reconcile reflects NetBox.
# Re-applying the seed on a later deploy is safe (idempotent) but the canonical
# place to change records post-bootstrap is NetBox.
#
# Built-in Provider Box service records (DNS, CA, Keycloak, NetBox, S3, SFTP,
# Syslog) are generated automatically from config/provider-box.env and must NOT
# be added here. Use this file only for external infrastructure (VCF nodes,
# gateways, vCenter, ESXi, etc.).
#
# Format:
# <fqdn> <ip>
# <fqdn> <ip/cidr>
#
# If you specify <ip/cidr>, Provider Box can derive the surrounding subnet and
# seed a NetBox prefix object in addition to an IP address object using the
# same subnet mask. The CIDR also drives reverse-zone selection for PTRs.
#
# If you specify only <ip>, Provider Box imports the host IP as /32 and does
# not guess the subnet.
#
# PTR records are generated automatically by the seed applier.

host32.sddc.lab 10.203.5.32/24
pod-240-vc01.sddc.lab 10.203.240.10/24
pod-240-nsx.sddc.lab 10.203.240.11/24
pod-240-ops.sddc.lab 10.203.240.13/24
pod-240-sddcm.sddc.lab 10.203.240.16/24
